 Center on the morning of September 11  2001  Attending VMI for one year  Mathers enlisted in the U S  Marines before serving in the U S  Navy from 1960 to 1966  In 1969 he began a career with Johnson   Higgins  where he started their nuclear power division  At the time of his death he was managing director of Marsh Power Group  Mathers served his community of Sea Girt  N J  as a volunteer firefighter for nearly 20 years  He retired as president of the Sea Girt Volunteer Fire Company in the mid 1990s  Charles Mathers is survived by his wife  Margaret  two daughters  Elizabeth Mathers and Marjorie Kane  one son  Charles Hood  and four grandchildren  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Charles W  Mathers  Class of 1962   Obituary  skip to content All Collections Limit to Historical Rosters Limit to Photographs VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Pro